Responsibilities

  Assist the Project Manager for the execution of contracts progress.
  Co-ordinate with clients, consultants, subcontractors to ensure timely delivery of schedule.
  Site co-ordination, monitoring and report work progress.
  Assist in the preparation, checking submission of shop drawings, as-built drawings, OMM etc.
  Assist Project Manager on all other project administrative matters.
  Carry out Green Building Certifications (training will be provided).
  Carry out Energy Audits (training will be provided).


Requirement

  Candidate must possess at least Diploma in Electrical / Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.
  Possess good interpersonal and communication skills.
  At least 2 year of relevant experience in M&amp;E projects.
  Knowledge in Green Building Certification (Green Mark) and Measurement and Verification System.
  Possess relevant safety certificates is an advantage.

Cushman &amp; Wakefield